    <title>[Review ongoing]Configure DHIS2 programs to work on Android apps</title>
    <para>To use event programs and tracker programs on the Android Event Capture and Tracker
        Capture apps, you must configure the programs in your
        <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161107T095657+0100" comment="DHIS2 web?
you DHIS2 web instance?"?>DHIS2<?oxy_comment_end?>
        web instance.</para>
    <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para>Create a user with the correct settings in DHIS2 web instance:</para>
            <orderedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Create a user.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Assign a user role that allow the user to access programs.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Assign programs to the user role.</para>
                </listitem>
            </orderedlist>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161114T113306+0100" comment="Reword."?>
            <para>Open the <emphasis role="bold">Program</emphasis> app and assign programs to
                organisation units. To work on an Andorid device you must have the same data capture
                and maintenance organisation unit as the organisation unit the program is assigned
                to.</para>
            <?oxy_comment_end?>
            <note>
                <para>It is important to only select the actual data capture organisation unit, if
                    you select the top organisation unit, the <emphasis role="bold">Event
                        Tracker</emphasis> and the <emphasis role="bold">Tracker Capture</emphasis>
                    Android apps, download ALL data for the organisation unit.</para>
            </note>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Open the relevant Android app and log in with the user you created.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para>Pull down to synch with the DHIS2
                <?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20161102T151130+0100" comment="Add screen shot."?>web<?oxy_comment_end?>
                instance.</para>
            <para>The app downloads all programs and organisation units the user has access
                to.</para>
        </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
